13年前为魔兽瘟疫写论文的玩家，如今正站在研究新冠病毒的第一线。
The player who wrote the paper for the plague 13 years ago is now on the front line of research for the new crown virus.
南回归线。
Tropic of Cancer.
文化。
Culture.
3天前。
Three days ago.
而另一个能帮助人们理解疫情的游戏已经玩不到了。
Another game that helps people understand the epidemic is over.
。
.
《魔兽世界》玩家想必基本都听说过这样一个故事：。
"World of Warcraft" players must have heard of such a story:
2005年，拥有将近400万玩家的《魔兽世界》中爆发了一场瘟疫。
In 2005, a plague broke out in World of Warcraft, which had nearly four million players.
因为暴雪设计上的疏漏，一种传染性极强的debuff在各大主城肆虐，在造成巨大伤亡的同时，引发了游戏中的社会混乱。
Because of the blizzard design omission, a highly infectious debuff in the major major cities, in addition to causing huge casualties, caused social chaos in the game.
。
.
这场在虚拟世界里发生的风波被称作“堕落之血事件”，一度得到公共卫生学界的关注，在接下来的数年间，被很多研究者作为流行病学的“虚拟案例”加以研究。
Known as the "blood of depravity," the virtual world was once the focus of public health circles and was studied by many researchers over the next few years as a "virtual case" of epidemiology.
。
.
当时，一名叫艾瑞克·洛夫格伦(Eric Lofgren)的美国大学生，以此事件撰写了一篇论文，主题是“虚拟世界如何协助研究现实中的传染病”，刊发于顶级医学期刊《柳叶刀·传染病》上。
Eric Lofgren, an American college student at the time, wrote a paper on how virtual worlds can help study infectious diseases in the real world, published in the top medical journal Lancet Infectious Diseases.
。
.
13年后，洛夫格伦已经从本科生变成了一名资深的流行病学家。
Thirteen years later, Lofgren has gone from undergraduate to senior epidemiologist.
在新冠疫情全球大流行的当下，他目前的主要工作是研究美国医疗体系如何应对新冠病毒的流行。
At a time of a global pandemic, his main task now is to study how the U. S. health-care system is responding to the new crown virus epidemic.
而近期他在接受采访时表明，2007年那篇关于《魔兽世界》的论文，至今仍然对普通人个体、乃至整个社会医疗卫生体系，有着非常的意义。
In a recent interview, he said that the 2007 paper on "World of Warcraft" is still of great significance to private individuals and to the entire social and health system.
。
.
我们不妨跟着洛夫格伦，从流行病学的视角重新回顾一遍“堕落之血”。
We might as well follow Lofgren and revisit the "Blood of Decline" from an epidemiological point of view.
（鉴于“堕落之血”事件已经广为流传，如果你早已熟知，可跳过下面这个章节从第二部分看起。
(Given that "blood of depravity" has become widespread, if you know it well enough, skip the following section to read the second part.)
）。
).
“堕落之血事件”始于2005年的9月13日。
The "Blood of Decline" began on Sept. 13, 2005.
或者更准确地说，是在《魔兽世界》1.7版本上线，“祖尔格拉布”副本正式开放这一天。
Or, to be more precise, on World of Warcraft version 1. 7, a copy of Zurgerab was officially opened that day.
。
.
“祖尔格拉布”副本的最终BOSS是“血神”哈卡，在战斗过程中，哈卡会向玩家释放名为“堕落之血”的负面法术，中招的玩家不仅会得到一个持续掉血的debuff，还会将其传染给一定距离内的队友。
The ultimate BOSS of the Zurgerab replica is the Haqqa, who unleashes a negative spell called "Fallen Blood" on the player, who not only receives a constantly bleeding debuff, but also infects his teammates over a distance.
。
.
不难看出，这个技能的目的是在限制玩家的走位。
It is easy to see that the purpose of this skill is to restrict the player's movement.
由于它造成的持续伤害极高，所以在暴雪的本意里，“堕落之血”只应该出现在这场BOSS战中，不太可能会被玩家带出副本。
Because of the continuing damage it does, Blizzard's original intent is that the "blood of depravity" should appear only in the BOSS war and is unlikely to be brought out by the player.
。
.
但暴雪的设计师忽略了自己的设计漏洞。
But Blizzard's designers ignored their own design flaws.
。
.
作为一个具备传染性的debuff，玩家角色并非“堕落之血”的唯一宿主——玩家的宠物也会感染“堕落之血”。
As an infectious debuff, the player's character is not the only host of "Fallen Blood" - the player's pet can also become infected with "fallen blood."
而宠物身上的debuff并不会因为解散消失，会在下次召唤时继续保留（这是为了防止玩家通过解散再召唤的手段达成“净化”的效果）。
The debuff on a pet does not disappear because it dissolves and will remain on the next summons (to prevent the player from achieving a "cleansing" effect by dissolving the summons).
。
.
于是，有玩家在副本中解散感染“堕落之血”的宠物，再去人口稠密的主城中把携带瘟疫的宠物召唤了出来——潘多拉魔盒就这样打开了。
Pandora's Box was thus opened when a player dissolved a pet infected with "Fallen Blood" in a replica and went to a densely populated main city to summon pets with the plague.
。
.
在洛夫格伦的研究中，肆虐艾泽拉斯的“堕落之血”，和现实中流行病传播的情形十分相似。
In Lofgren's study, the "blood of depravity" that ravaged Azeroth is very similar to what happens when an epidemic spreads.
。
.
比如，游戏中的玩家都拥有远距离移动的手段，这是“堕落之血”快速传播的基础。
For example, the players in the game have the means to move far away, which is the basis of the rapid spread of "depraved blood."
很多感染了的玩家在死亡或是治愈前将自己传送到其他主城，进而把瘟疫传染给了更多的角色。
Many infected players transmit themselves to other major cities before they die or heal, thus infecting more characters with the plague.
。
.
而在历史上，不论是中世纪的黑死病还是19世纪的霍乱，其跨地域流行都是因为病毒携带者的长途旅行。
Historically, the cross-regional epidemic of either the medieval or nineteenth-century cholera was due to the long journeys of virus carriers.
。
.
而《魔兽世界》里众多回血速度超过掉血速度的NPC，类似于现实中的“无症状携带者”。
In World of Warcraft, many of the NPC, which is bleeding faster than losing blood, resemble asymptomatic carriers in reality.
尽管他们始终在向周围散播病毒，看起来却很健康，进而对瘟疫的传播也起到了一定的促进作用。
Although they have been spreading the virus around, they seem to be healthy, contributing to the spread of the disease.
。
.
于是，几乎牢不可破的感染链就这么在NPC、玩家以及宠物间中形成了。
As a result, almost unbreakable chains of infection form in NPCs, players, and pets.
。
.
哈卡、感染人群、未感染人群、宠物、NPC之间的复杂传播关系。
Complex communication relationships between haka, infected population, uninfected population, pets, NPC.
瘟疫传播的过程中，拥有更高血量的高等级玩家往往是相对安全的，真正惨死街头的大多是些低等级玩家。
As the plague spreads, high-level players with higher blood levels tend to be relatively safe, and the truly gruesome ones are mostly low-level players.
就像现实中的易感人群（儿童、老人以及免疫力受损患者）一样，贫瘠的血条注定这些人无法在瘟疫面前久久支撑。
Just as in the real world of susceptible people (children, the elderly, and people with impaired immunity), poor blood strips are bound to keep these people afloat for long.
。
.
尸横遍野的情景带来的是更彻底的混乱，游戏世界本来就没什么稳定的社会结构，瘟疫下的玩家更是陷入了疯狂。
The spectacle of carnage leads to more complete chaos, with no stable social structure in the game world, and a plague of players in madness.
。
.
唯恐天下不乱的人开始主动散播瘟疫，这种现实中的“反社会行为”在游戏里并不会遭到过重的谴责，毕竟游戏中的死亡不是真正的死亡。
The real-life "anti-social behavior" doesn't get too much blame in the game because death in the game is not really death.
。
.
不少善良的治疗职业玩家主动向低血量的感染者伸出援手，使其不至于倒毙当场。
Many good-hearted professional players actively to low blood volume of infected people to help them not to fall on the spot.
这确实切降低了传染病的死亡率，但并不能阻止疫情进一步发展：存活下来的感染者获得了更多的时间去散播疾病，就连治疗者自身也可能遭遇“患者”的感染。
This has certainly reduced mortality from infectious diseases, but it has not stopped the epidemic from spreading: those who survive are given more time to spread the disease, and even those who do manage to treat themselves are likely to be infected.
。
.
疫情影响下，越来越多的玩家无法正常进行游戏。
Due to the epidemic, more and more players are unable to play games properly.
暴雪起初想通过隔离的手段限制瘟疫，但就像前面所说的，这只是个游戏，开发商无法进行强制的地区封锁，玩家也对“隔离”普遍抱有抵制态度。
Blizzard initially tried to contain the plague by isolating it, but, as mentioned earlier, it was a game in which developers could not enforce a regional blockade and players generally resisted "quarantining."
。
.
最终，暴雪只能通过更新补丁彻底抹去了“堕落之血”的传染性，让它变成了一个再普通不过的直伤技能。
In the end, Blizzard can only be updated to completely wipe out the "depraved blood" infectivity, making it a very common straight-wound skill.
。
.
尽管这场闹剧最终被暴雪以一种现实中无法效仿的方式掐断，但其呈现出的人类对流行病的真实反映却是具备研究价值的。
Although the farce was finally blocked by Blizzard in a way that could not be emulated in reality, its real response to epidemic is worth studying.
。
.
也因此，当时身为《魔兽世界》玩家的洛夫格伦在一位教授的协助下，把自己亲身经历的这场“瘟疫”写成了论文，最终刊发到了最顶级的医学期刊上。
So Lofgren, who was a World of Warcraft player at the time, wrote his paper on the plague and published it in top medical journals with the help of a professor.
。
.
值得一提的是，洛夫格伦的本科学的是生物学，学习方向原本和流行病毫无关系。
It is worth mentioning that Lofgren's original science is biology, and the direction of study had nothing to do with epidemics.
但在2007年毕业后，他选择去念公共卫生的硕士（MSPH），并在之后一直从事公共卫生和流行病领域的研究。
But after graduating in 2007, he chose to pursue a Master's degree in public health (MSPH), and since then has been doing research in the areas of public health and epidemiology.
。
.
这是否是由于“堕落之血事件”的影响，我们不得而知。
Whether this is due to the "depraved blood incident" influence, we do not know.
但总之，在多年以后，洛夫格伦成为了一名流行病学领域的专家，目前就职于华盛顿州立大学。
But after years, Lofgren became an expert in epidemiology and now works at Washington State University.
。
.
恰好，新冠病毒在全球大面积爆发后，华盛顿州成为了美国疫情最严重的地区之一。
As it happens, Washington State became one of the worst affected areas in the United States after the global outbreak of the new crown virus.
。
.
图自《世界日报》，左上角最鲜红的那块即华盛顿州。
Pictured in The World Daily, Washington State is the scarlet section in the upper left corner.
自疫情爆发以来，洛夫格伦的研究重心很快就转移到了新冠病毒身上。
Since the outbreak, Lofgren's research has quickly shifted to the new crown virus.
目前，他的主要工作是研究新冠病毒对美国医疗体系到底会产生多大影响。
His main task now is to see how much impact the new crown virus will have on America's health care system.
。
.
他通过收集分析数据来判断病人住院时是否需要呼吸机、病患是否可能将疾病传染给照顾他的医护人员……“我是流行病学家，研究新型传染病是我的专长”，洛夫格伦在接受媒体采访时如此说道。
He collected and analyzed data to determine whether the patient needed a ventilator while in hospital, and whether he was likely to transmit the disease to his paramedics... "I'm an epidemiologist and it's my specialty to study new infections," Lofgren told the media.
。
.
洛夫格伦看来，他在2007年所著的那篇论文，与他当下的工作存在着重要的相似之处，即“人们应对疫情的行为会严重影响疫情的流行情况”。
According to Lofgren, his 2007 paper bears an important resemblance to his current work: "The way people respond to the epidemic can seriously affect the epidemic."
。
.
新冠肆虐的大背景下，人与人之间如何交互、政府下达的规章制度是否能够严格执行，都会影响疫情的传播速度。
In the context of the new crown, how people interact with each other and whether the rules and regulations issued by the government can be strictly enforced will affect the spread of the epidemic.
。
.
现实中可能罕有“堕落之血事件”中那样主动散播病毒的玩家，但像“我就去看个球”、“我就去聚个餐”这样的人却不在少数。
In reality there may be few players who actively spread the virus as in the "Blood of the Fall" case, but there are many like "I'll go see a ball" and "I'll go get a meal."
即便他们没有传播疾病的主观意图，但其行为带来的后果却可能同样严重。
Even if they do not have a subjective intention to spread the disease, the consequences of their actions can be no less severe.
。
.
洛夫格伦还指出，2018年，流行病学领域的不少顶尖专家离开了美国。
In 2018, says Lofgren, leading experts in epidemiology left the country.
这使得过去的几年里，美国对流行病的反应速度下降了。
This has led to a decline in the United States' response to epidemics over the past few years.
。
.
他用《魔兽世界》举了个例子，“在游戏中，玩家始终懂得积累物资应对接下来的挑战，尽管这不一定有用，但做好准备永远是必须的。
He used "World of Warcraft" as an example. "In a game, players always know how to accumulate supplies to meet the challenges that lie ahead.
……这就像即便地震有阵子没来，也不能抛弃预测地震的人，地震总是会来的。
... It's like not being able to abandon people who have predicted earthquakes even if they haven't been here for a while.
”。
"
作为2007年那篇论文的第二作者（与洛夫格伦合作的那位教授），妮娜·费弗曼(Nina Fefferman)今天也在田纳西大学与各地学者共同研究新冠病毒。
As co-author of the 2007 paper (the professor who collaborated with Lofgren), Nina Fefferman is also working today at the University of Tennessee with scholars around the world on the new crown virus.
在她看来，曾经对“堕落之血事件”的调查研究即使放在今天依旧没有过时。
In her view, the study of the "blood of depravity" is not out of date even today.
。
.
Eric Lofgren（左）与Nina Fefferman（右）。
Eric Lofgren (left) and Nina Fefferman (right).
“那使我真正深入地去思考人们怎样看待威胁，以及看待威胁方式的不同会怎样影响他们的行为。
"That gives me a real insight into how people view threats and how different ways of looking at them affect their behavior.
在那之后，我花费了很大的工夫去构建风险感知的社会结构模型。
Since then, I have spent a great deal of time constructing social structure models of risk perception.
如果没有对‘堕落之血事件’的了解与调查研究，我的工作会比现在艰难得多。
My work would have been much more difficult without the knowledge and investigation of the 'Blood of the Fall'.
”。
"
如今，就像“堕落之血事件”在魔兽玩家中口耳相传一样，有关新冠的一切话题也在各路社交媒体上展开。
Now, just as "The Blood of the Fall" has been whispered about among Warcraft players, all the talk about the new crown has spread across social media.
费弗曼表示，在美国，她有关新冠检测的研究受到了极大的阻力，这意味着美国真实的新冠病例数，或许会比人们目前所知的要多得多。
In the US, she says, her research on new crown jewels has been met with a great deal of resistance, which means there may be many more new cases in the country than is currently known.
。
.
关于2007年那篇论文的故事，就到此为止了。
This is the end of the story about the 2007 paper.
。
.
长久以来，学界一直有人反对将“堕落之血事件”与流行病学研究联系起来。
There has long been academic opposition to the association of "depraved blood events" with epidemiological studies.
用洛夫格伦的话来说，“总有人认为游戏中那种纯粹以作恶为乐的玩家在现实中并不存在，游戏中的灾难不会也无法在现实世界中重演。
In Lofgren's words, "there is always the belief that the game's purely evil-playing players do not exist in reality, and that the game's catastrophes do not and cannot be repeated in the real world.
”。
"
的确，游戏只是游戏，我们也常这么说。
Yes, games are just games, as we often say.
但有的时候，游戏突然就变成了现实的一面镜子。
But sometimes, the game suddenly becomes a mirror of reality.
。
.
作为一个老玩家，洛夫格伦最近也没落下《魔兽世界》怀旧服。
As a veteran gamer, Lofgren hasn't fallen into World of Warcraft nostalgia lately.
据他所说，即使在今天，魔兽玩家们也经常提到“堕落之血事件”，并暗暗期待暴雪连带着把瘟疫也“怀旧”一次。
Even today, according to him, Warcraft players often refer to the "blood of depravity" and secretly expect a blizzard to be accompanied by "nostalgia" for the plague.
很明显，玩家渴望进一步了解传染病，不论是站在病毒的角度，还是站在人类的角度。
Clearly, players are eager to learn more about infectious diseases, both from a virus perspective and from a human perspective.
。
.
当年引发“堕落之血事件”的副本——祖尔格拉布，确实即将加入怀旧服了。
Zurab, a copy of the "blood of depravity" that year, is indeed about to join the nostalgic.
只不过，和十几年前相比，今天的战场，并不仅仅在艾泽拉斯之内。
But today's battlefield is not just Azeroth, compared to more than a decade ago.
。
.
（本文部分资料来自PC GAMER对Eric Lofgren和Nina Fefferman的采访）。
(Part of this information is from PC GAMER's interview with Eric Lofgren and Nina Fefferman).
